HEADWORD: introversive
<hw>introversive</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Psychol.)</fld>
<def>directed inward; marked by interest in oneself or concerned with
inner feelings. Contrasted with <ant>extroversive</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>introvert, introverted, introvertive</stype>;
<stype>introvertish, shut-in </stype>]. Antonym: <ant>ambiversive</ant>.
<see>Also See: <er>unsociable</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
